{"comments":"SemanticElevation — meaningful elevation scale for UI depth.\n\n## The Problem\n\nCSS provides box-shadow with raw pixel values, but humans think in\nsemantic terms: \"this card should float above the page\", \"this modal\nshould be the topmost layer\", \"this button should look pressed\".\n\n## The Solution\n\nThis module provides a bounded, semantic elevation scale (0-5) that:\n\n- Maps to research-backed shadow configurations\n- Provides consistent depth perception across UI\n- Scales proportionally for different contexts\n- Works with both light and dark themes\n\n## Elevation Levels\n\n| Level | Name     | Use Case                          | Z-Index Range |\n|-------|----------|-----------------------------------|---------------|\n| 0     | Flat     | Recessed, inset, pressed states   | 0-99          |\n| 1     | Raised   | Cards, list items, default state  | 100-199       |\n| 2     | Floating | Dropdowns, tooltips, popovers     | 200-299       |\n| 3     | Overlay  | Sidebars, drawers, panels         | 300-399       |\n| 4     | Modal    | Dialogs, modals                   | 400-499       |\n| 5     | Toast    | Notifications, toasts, top layer  | 500-599       |\n\n## Research Basis\n\nShadow configurations follow Material Design research on perceived\nelevation, with modifications for modern aesthetics (softer, more\ndiffuse shadows characteristic of Linear, Vercel, and similar UIs).\n\n## Usage\n\n```purescript\nimport Hydrogen.Schema.Elevation.SemanticElevation as SE\n\n-- Get shadow for a specific elevation\ncardShadow = SE.shadowForLevel SE.Raised\n\n-- Convert to CSS\ncss = SE.toLegacyCss SE.Modal\n```\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[126,9],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/SemanticElevation.purs","start":[126,3]},"title":"Flat"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[127,11],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/SemanticElevation.purs","start":[127,3]},"title":"Raised"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[128,13],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/SemanticElevation.purs","start":[128,3]},"title":"Floating"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[129,12],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/SemanticElevation.purs","start":[129,3]},"title":"Overlay"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[130,10],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/SemanticElevation.purs","start":[130,3]},"title":"Modal"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[131,10],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/SemanticElevation.purs","start":[131,3]},"title":"Toast"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Elevation","SemanticElevation"],"ElevationLevel"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[133,54],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/SemanticElevation.purs","start":[133,1]},"title":"eqElevationLevel"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Elevation","SemanticElevation"],"ElevationLevel"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[134,56],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/SemanticElevation.purs","start":[134,1]},"title":"ordElevationLevel"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Elevation","SemanticElevation"],"ElevationLevel"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[142,23],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/SemanticElevation.purs","start":[136,1]},"title":"showElevationLevel"}],"comments":"Semantic elevation level — bounded from 0 (flat) to 5 (toast).\n\nEach level represents a distinct plane in the UI's z-axis hierarchy.\nThe scale is intentionally limited to prevent elevation inflation\n(where everything becomes \"important\" and nothing stands out).\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"data","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[131,10],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/SemanticElevation.purs","start":[125,1]},"title":"ElevationLevel"},{"children":[],"comments":"All elevation levels in ascending order\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Array"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Elevation","SemanticElevation"],"ElevationLevel"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[153,34],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/SemanticElevation.purs","start":[153,1]},"title":"allLevels"},{"children":[],"comments":"Convert level to integer (0-5)\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Elevation","SemanticElevation"],"ElevationLevel"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[157,36],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/SemanticElevation.purs","start":[157,1]},"title":"levelToInt"},{"children":[],"comments":"Convert integer to level (clamped to 0-5)\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Elevation","SemanticElevation"],"ElevationLevel"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[166,38],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/SemanticElevation.purs","start":[166,1]},"title":"levelFromInt"},{"children":[],"comments":"Type aliases for clarity in function signatures\n","info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"typeSynonym","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Elevation","SemanticElevation"],"ElevationLevel"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[145,27],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/SemanticElevation.purs","start":[145,1]},"title":"Flat"},{"children":[],"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"typeSynonym","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Elevation","SemanticElevation"],"ElevationLevel"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[146,29],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/SemanticElevation.purs","start":[146,1]},"title":"Raised"},{"children":[],"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"typeSynonym","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Elevation","SemanticElevation"],"ElevationLevel"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[147,31],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/SemanticElevation.purs","start":[147,1]},"title":"Floating"},{"children":[],"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"typeSynonym","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Elevation","SemanticElevation"],"ElevationLevel"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[148,30],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/SemanticElevation.purs","start":[148,1]},"title":"Overlay"},{"children":[],"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"typeSynonym","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Elevation","SemanticElevation"],"ElevationLevel"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[149,28],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/SemanticElevation.purs","start":[149,1]},"title":"Modal"},{"children":[],"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"typeSynonym","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Elevation","SemanticElevation"],"ElevationLevel"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[150,28],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/SemanticElevation.purs","start":[150,1]},"title":"Toast"},{"children":[],"comments":"Get LayeredShadow for an elevation level (light theme).\n\nShadows use multiple layers for realistic depth:\n- Ambient shadow: Soft, diffuse background shadow\n- Key shadow: Sharper, directional shadow (light from above)\n\n## Research Notes\n\nThese configurations follow observations from Linear, Vercel, Stripe,\nand other modern UIs. Key characteristics:\n\n- Lower opacity than Material Design (more subtle)\n- Larger blur radii relative to offset (softer edges)\n- Negative spread to prevent shadow \"halo\" effect\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Elevation","SemanticElevation"],"ElevationLevel"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Elevation","Shadow"],"LayeredShadow"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[194,50],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/SemanticElevation.purs","start":[194,1]},"title":"shadowForLevel"},{"children":[],"comments":"Get LayeredShadow for an elevation level (dark theme).\n\nDark themes require different shadow treatment:\n- Higher opacity shadows (to be visible against dark backgrounds)\n- Often combined with subtle borders or glows\n- Same structure, different color values\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Elevation","SemanticElevation"],"ElevationLevel"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Elevation","Shadow"],"LayeredShadow"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[224,54],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/SemanticElevation.purs","start":[224,1]},"title":"shadowForLevelDark"},{"children":[],"comments":"Get the base z-index for an elevation level.\n\nEach level occupies a 100-unit range, allowing for sub-layering\nwithin a level (e.g., dropdown at 200, dropdown item at 201).\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Elevation","SemanticElevation"],"ElevationLevel"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[254,36],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/SemanticElevation.purs","start":[254,1]},"title":"zIndexBase"},{"children":[],"comments":"Get the z-index range for an elevation level.\n\nReturns {min, max} for the level's z-index range.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeCon